race.comment: EYE OF THE FIRE (1) gets the gun run again after finishing over the top of them first-up with a decisive victory over 1100m at Randwick. Goes just as well second-up and is adept in all conditions. ART'S ALIVE (9) good fresh mare resuming. Proven at this level and the two sound trials suggest she could be forward enough for a first-up win. Genuine each way contender. MASSIRA (11) drops in weight with the claim and strips fitter fourth-up. Can figure in the minor money. BEV'S NINE (7) was very impressive in his debut campaign and his three wins all came on different going. Form out of his efforts last campaign stack up and he's sure to be in the finish if he can run up to his trial efforts.
